headline: Titans Put End to Patriots’ Season, and Maybe an Era
abstract: A wild-card defeat stifled New England’s pursuit of a record-breaking seventh Super Bowl title. Did it also spell the end of the Belichick-Brady era?
lead_paragraph: FOXBOROUGH, Mass. — The New England Patriots’ quest for a record seventh Super Bowl championship ended abruptly Saturday night at Gillette Stadium with a 20-13 upset loss to the Tennessee Titans in the wild-card round of the N.F.L. playoffs. The defeat for the defending Super Bowl champions was a startling setback at home, where New England has won 20 out of 24 postseason games over the last two decades.
